hopobject.body: A financial advisor what is lamisil The 150-foot-wide Project Olympus stations would spin four times per minute to create acceleration in their arms. On each station, the crew deck farthest from the hub would experience the greatest acceleration: the equivalent of one-quarter of Earth’s gravitational pull, or about midway between lunar and martian surface gravity. Crew decks closer to the hub would experience less acceleration. Olling hinted that the different levels of acceleration the astronauts would experience on decks at varying distances from the hub might be useful for scientific research, but he provided no specifics.
